    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nIn Python 3.12, the legacy Unicode API is removed; see https://docs.python.org/3.12/whatsnew/3.12.html#id9. Using the `Py_UNICODE` struct would lead to using deprecated APIs which are removed in 3.12. I think it would be better if the docs were updated to not use it.\r\n\r\nURL: https://docs.cython.org/en/latest/src/tutorial/strings.html#windows-and-wide-character-apis",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You probably noticed the big red warning in that section. Seems worth adding a note about the status in Python 3.12 there, also specifically on Windows.\n\nI don't think we should remove that section any time soon, not even in Cython 3.1. Python 3.12 and later are far from adopted and older Python versions make use of Py_UNICODE, especially on Windows.\n",
